<h1>SKK Openlab Mailing list -- Discussions on SKK dictionaries, servers and front ends.</h1>

<div id="langswitch"><a href="ml-ja.html">Japanese</a></div>

<h2>About SKK Openlab mailing list</h2>

<p>This list is for communications among SKK users including developers of dictionaries, servers and front ends.</p>

<p>To see the collection of prior postings to the list, visit the <a href="http://mail.ring.gr.jp/skk">SKK Openlab list archives</a>.</p>

<h2>Using SKK Openlab mailing list</h2>

<p>To post a message to all the list members, send email to <a href="mailto:skk@ring.gr.jp">skk@ring.gr.jp</a>.

<p>Note that you need to subscribe to the list before posting a message.</p>

<h2>Subscribing to SKK Openlab mailing list</h2>

<p>When you send email to ezmlm, you should leave both the subject header and the body empty.  Please contact <a href="mailto:skk-owner@ring.gr.jp">skk-owner@ring.gr.jp</a> for any trouble.</p>

<h3>Subscribe</h3>

<p>Send email to <a href="mailto:skk-subscribe@ring.gr.jp">skk-subscribe@ring.gr.jp</a>.  You will be sent email requesting confirmation, to prevent others from gratuitously subscribing you.</p>

<h3>Subscribe as a post only member (i.e. ML messages are not delivered to you)</h3>

<p>Send email to skk-allow-subscribe-USER=DOMAIN@ring.gr.jp and reply to the confirmation email.  For example, if your address is foo@bar.net, send email to skk-allow-subscribe-foo=bar.net@ring.gr.jp.</p>

<h2>Ezmlm commands for subscribers</h2>

<h3>Unsubscribe</h3>

<p>Send email to <a href="mailto:skk-unsubscribe@ring.gr.jp">skk-unsubscribe@ring.gr.jp</a>.  You will be sent email requesting confirmation.</p>

<h3>Change the email address</h3>
<p>Unsubscribe, and subscribe again with a new address.</p>

<h3>Unsubscription of a post only member</h3>
<p>Send email to skk-allow-unsubscribe-USER=DOMAIN@ring.gr.jp and reply to the confirmation email.</p>

<h2>Newsgroup</h2>
<p>You can read mailing list messages via NNTP.  Host name is "news.ring.gr.jp".  Newsgroup is "ring.openlab.skk".</p>

<p>There is a restriction in the ring news service.  Although a cross post to multiple mailing lists within the ring openlab is valid and normally delivered, it will be rejected by the ring news server, since it is regarded as multiple posts with the same Message-ID.</p>

